            <div type="a">
                <column>1</column>
                <head>To the Polls! To the Polls!</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt>We should not adopt the hackneyed stereotyped caption "To the Polls" in
                    these last words of exhortation to the voters of Augusta, if we did not feel
                    more sensibly than usual that everything depends, in this election, upon their
                    going to the polls on Thursday.</excerpt>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Emphasizes the need for Augusta Whigs and Americans to vote against the
                    Democrats on Thursday. Goes through a bunch of issues.</summary>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>3</column>
                <head>Scarcity</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>The hard winter has resulted in a local grain shortage. Augusta may need to
                    import flour from Richmond before the harvest.</summary>
            </div>
            <pageNote>Lots about the upcoming election.</pageNote>
        </page>
